QA report written to `minesweeper/QA_REPORT.md`.

**GAME: minesweeper — SCORE: 9/10 — VERDICT: PASS**

Summary: Loads cleanly, portal back-link (`../index.html`) works, localStorage best-times persist per difficulty, all text English, first-click safety + chord + flood-fill all correct, mobile viewport uses horizontal scroll on Intermediate/Expert.

Real bugs (minor):
1. Long-press flag can double-toggle on some Android browsers (native `contextmenu` fires after the 350ms touchstart setTimeout, and the contextmenu handler toggles again) — missing `-webkit-touch-callout: none` and no guard.
2. Mouse clicks silently ignored on touch-capable laptops in Firefox/older Safari because `click` is a `MouseEvent` (no `pointerType`), making the `'ontouchstart' in window && e.pointerType !== 'mouse'` guard always return early.
3. `.app > *:nth-child(7)` (Best Times) has no `animation-delay`, breaking the fade-in stagger.
4. Dead calls: `checkWin()` inside `toggleFlag()`; empty `mousedown` handler.
5. Onboarding message only mentions touch — desktop users aren't told right-click flags.

No crashes, no layout collapse, no broken core flow. Ship-ready; fixes 1–3 are worth doing, 4–6 are polish.
